    caption: [The Weddell seal (Leptonychotes weddellii), though clumsy on land, can dive to over 500 meters depth and remain submerged for up to an hour and 20 minutes. The Adélie penguin (Pygoscelis adeliae) must overcome the buoyancy of its plumage to descend, but that buoyancy also allows it to ascend rapidly.],
