    caption: [Mangroves have adaptations for coping with a high salt load. (a) The roots of mangroves are immersed in salt water at high tide. (b) Specialized glands in the leaves of the button mangrove (Conocarpus erecta) excrete salt, which precipitates on their outer surfaces.],
